2026-04-08 | Segregate 0s and 1s

	Question
Modify the array so that all 0s are on the left and 1s on the right.

	Approach
1.	Use two pointers:
		left → start of array  
		right → end of array  

2.	While left < right:
		- If left is 0 → move left forward  
		- If right is 1 → move right backward  
		- If left is 1 and right is 0:
				swap them  

3.	Continue until pointers meet.

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    void segregate(vector<int>& arr) {

        int left = 0;
        int right = arr.size() - 1;

        while(left < right){

            if(arr[left] == 0){
                left++;
            }
            else if(arr[right] == 1){
                right--;
            }
            else{
                swap(arr[left], arr[right]);
                left++;
                right--;
            }
        }
    }
};

	Key Insight
This is a classic **two-pointer partitioning problem**.  
We push 0s to the left and 1s to the right in a single pass without extra space.
